STRATEGY PROMPT
Use and follow the role definition from paid-media-strategist-construct as your baseline identity and thinking style.
All outputs must follow the global project instructions already defined in this Claude project.
You must read and interpret the following input files directly from the Claude project environment:
brief.csv
Authoritative source for: campaign objective, target audience, programme/product details, markets, constraints, timeline, business context, expected outcomes.
All strategic interpretation must come strictly from brief.csv.
Raw GitHub reference:
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/levi51097/paid-media-automation-construct/main/schema/brief.csv
tactic_library.csv
Contains the complete list of Construct Digital paid media tactics.
Each row includes funnel stage, channel, format, and tactic name.
All tactics in the Campaign Flow must be selected directly from tactic_library.csv.
Raw GitHub reference: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/levi51097/paid-media-automation-construct/main/schema/tactic_library.csv
Reference Material Policy
Uploaded Construct proposals (Step IT Up, NUS AIDF, NUS Stanford, Toll, etc.) may be used only for structural inspiration.
Do not copy or paraphrase any content (messages, flows, personas, CTAs, wording, or insight).
All output must be original and based only on the CSV inputs.
Objective
Generate a clean, structured, executive-ready holistic campaign strategy.
No numeric forecasting, budget modelling, or performance projection of any kind.
OUTPUT STRUCTURE (FOLLOW EXACTLY)
1. Campaign Overview
Provide a concise strategic interpretation of the brief:
Core objective


High-level audience description


High-level programme description


Key markets


Campaign mode: Budget-Driven or KPI-Driven
 Describe how the mode affects strategic direction.
 No numeric KPIs and no repetition of brief text.
2. Audience Segmentation and Personas
Interpret audience information from brief.csv.
 Segmentation rules:
Use one segment if audience differences are minimal


Only segment when behaviour/motivation/intent differ meaningfully
 For each valid segment, provide:


Demographics


Professional context


Motivations


Pain points


Decision barriers


Intent behaviours


Messaging triggers
 Keep concise and actionable.


3. Recommended Channel Mix
List channels without ranking or qualifiers.
 For each channel provide only:
Strategic role


Why it fits the audience’s behaviour
 Do not include tactics or formats.
4. Conversion Funnel Architecture
Use Construct Digital’s funnel: Prospecting → Retargeting → Nurturing
 For each stage specify:
Stage objective


Mindset + psychological shift


CTA


KPI type (Traffic, MQL, SQL, Application, etc.)


Campaign type (Prospecting / Retargeting / Nurturing)
 Do not include tactics, numeric KPIs, movement logic, or pacing.
5. Messaging Structure
Provide:
Umbrella messaging


Prospecting messaging (segmented only if meaningful segments exist)


1–2 Retargeting messages


1–2 Nurturing messages
 Messages should be directional, not copywriting.


6. Campaign Flow
Use tactic_library.csv to select tactics for each funnel stage.
 Output must be clean, visual, structured, and deck-ready.
Strict rules:
Bullet lists only


No sentences


No explanations


No behaviour descriptions


No commentary


No transitions


No qualifiers (essential/recommended/etc.)


No numeric KPIs


No timeline or pacing


Each bullet must follow format: Channel: Tactic Name


Use only tactics from tactic_library.csv


Content must be fully original


Required structure:
Prospecting
Channel: Tactic Name


Channel: Tactic Name


Channel: Tactic Name


Retargeting
Channel: Tactic Name


Channel: Tactic Name


Channel: Tactic Name


Nurturing
Channel: Tactic Name


Channel: Tactic Name


Channel: Tactic Name


STYLE REQUIREMENTS
Strategic, concise, structured, senior tone.
No fluff, filler, clichés, or restating the prompt.
No numeric modelling.
All content must be original.
FINAL INSTRUCTION
After reading brief.csv and tactic_library.csv, generate a fully original campaign strategy strictly following the structure above and adhering to the reference policy.
No disclaimers or apologies.
Output must be deck-ready.
